1. COLOR PALETTE — REQUIRED RULES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Define two brand colors:
  BRAND_DARK  = the product's primary dark color (used for section banners, title)
  BRAND_ACCENT = the product's highlight/action color (used for HR line, label_style,
                 title_sub_style, callout accent bar)

WCAG 4.5:1 CONTRAST IS MANDATORY on all text. Before writing styles:
  - Compute luminance for every text/background pair using the sRGB formula
  - If BRAND_ACCENT on white < 4.5:1, define BRAND_TEXT = a darker shade that passes,
    and use BRAND_TEXT for ALL text; reserve BRAND_ACCENT for decorative elements only
    (HR lines, table backgrounds, left-bar accents, colored circles)
  - Never use a color for text that you haven't verified passes 4.5:1

Required neutral colors (use these exact hex values):
  LTGRAY = #F4F6F8   MGRAY  = #D0D5DD   DKGRAY = #344054
  CGRAY  = #667085   AMBER  = #FFF8E1

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
2. PARAGRAPH STYLES — REQUIRED NAMES AND SPECS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Define all of these — do not rename or omit any:

  body_style       Helvetica 9.5pt DKGRAY TA_JUSTIFY leading=14 spaceAfter=6
  bullet_style     Helvetica 9.5pt DKGRAY TA_LEFT    leading=14 leftIndent=12 spaceAfter=4
  label_style      Helvetica-Bold 8.5pt BRAND_ACCENT (verify 4.5:1) TA_LEFT leading=13 spaceBefore=8 spaceAfter=3
  caption_style    Helvetica-Oblique 8pt CGRAY TA_CENTER leading=11 spaceAfter=6
  footer_style     Helvetica 7.5pt CGRAY TA_CENTER leading=10
  title_main_style Helvetica-Bold 22pt BRAND_DARK leading=26 spaceAfter=4
  title_sub_style  Helvetica 10pt BRAND_ACCENT (verify 4.5:1) leading=14 spaceAfter=6
  th_style         Helvetica-Bold 9pt WHITE TA_LEFT leading=12   ← used in ALL table headers
  td_style         Helvetica 9pt DKGRAY TA_LEFT leading=12
  td_bold_style    Helvetica-Bold 9pt DKGRAY TA_LEFT leading=12
  td_center_style  Helvetica 9pt DKGRAY TA_CENTER leading=12
  snap_label_style Helvetica-Bold 9pt WHITE TA_LEFT leading=12   ← snapshot table col 0 only

  W = 6.3 * inch   (usable width — do NOT change this)

