5. REQUIRED DOCUMENT STRUCTURE (in order)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Every report must contain these sections in this order.
Section names are descriptive, not numbered.

  TITLE BLOCK
    • Product name in title_main_style
    • One-line descriptor in title_sub_style  
      format: "[Tagline] · Product Overview · [Month Year]"
    • HRFlowable width=W thickness=1.5 color=BRAND_ACCENT spaceAfter=10

  WHAT IT IS
    • 2–4 sentence paragraph in body_style
    • 2-column snapshot table (colWidths=[1.6in, 4.7in]):
      - Header row: uses th_style in BOTH columns on BRAND_DARK background
      - Col 0 data cells: snap_label_style (white bold) — BRAND_DARK background applied
        via TableStyle BACKGROUND command per row in a loop
      - Col 1 data cells: td_style — alternating white/LTGRAY backgrounds
      - Rows: URL, AI Feature, Grades, Free Tier, Pricing, Login options, Key stats
        (add/remove rows as appropriate for the product)
    • 1–2 screenshots (side_by_side or img_full)
    • 1 callout box (UNLIKE or UNIQUE as appropriate)

  HOW IT WORKS  
    • subsection labels in label_style (no section_header banner)
    • bullet lists in bullet_style
    • screenshots inline after each subsection they illustrate
    • callout boxes (UNLIKE/UNIQUE) after any finding that differentiates from Newsela Writing


 HOW IT MATCHES UP (side by side comparisons with Newsela Writing)
    • subsection labels in label_style (no section_header banner)
    • bullet lists in bullet_style
    • screenshots inline after each subsection they illustrate
    • callout boxes (UNLIKE/UNIQUE) after any finding that differentiates from Newsela Writing

  AI [FEATURE NAME]  (e.g. "AI GRADING ASSISTANT" or "AI WRITING COACH")
    • Description paragraph
    • UNLIKE NEWSELA callout about feedback timing
    • Screenshot(s) of the AI feature
    • Data table if applicable (rubric criteria, category breakdown, etc.)
    • UNIQUE callout for any differentiating capability

  LIVE AI TEST FINDINGS (Month Year)
    • "Two essays were submitted to probe [AI feature] scoring…" opening paragraph
    • For each test:
      - label_style subsection header: "Test N — Input: [description]"
      - Body paragraph describing the input
      - side_by_side screenshots (input + output)
      - Findings labeled in label_style: "Finding N — [Title]: [subtitle]"
      - Comparison table if applicable (colWidths proportional, BRAND_DARK header row)
      - UNIQUE or UNLIKE callout for each key finding

  ADDITIONAL FEATURES (add any features that do not overlap Newsela Writing)
    • UNIQUE callout at top of section
    • subsection labels for additional features
    • bullet lists for each feature
    • screenshots inline

  FREE VS. PREMIUM  (or FREE MODEL if fully free)
    • UNLIKE NEWSELA callout at top
    • Free/Premium feature comparison table or bullet lists
